EX1¶

In this exercise I wanted to rank the following functions by their order of growth. The functions are: 2lgn, n3, lgn, en, n, n2, lg(n!), 2n, n!, 22^n, ln(n), (n + 1)!, nlg(n), 1, 22^(n+1)

Conclusions:¶

Based on the plot above the O(1) is the best then O(ln) then O(lgn) then O(n) then O(nlogn) then O(2lgn) then O(lg(n!)) then O(n^2) then O(n^3) then O(2^n) then O(2^2^n) then O(2^2^(n+1)) then O(n!) O(e^n) then O((n + 1)!)
